![medium](https://www.gstatic.com/codereviewagent/medium-priority.svg)

The `env` Proxy's `get` trap will attempt to call `getEnvServer()` for any property access that doesn't start with `VITE_`. This includes standard object properties like `toString`, `toJSON`, or `constructor` if they are accessed by framework internals or devtools. In a browser environment, `getEnvServer()` will trigger a Zod validation failure and crash the application because server-side environment variables are missing. The trap should explicitly handle symbols and properties existing on `Object.prototype` before delegating to environment loaders.

```suggestion
export const env = new Proxy({} as Env, {
  get: (target, property) => {
    if (typeof property === 'symbol' || property in Object.prototype) {
      return (target as any)[property];
    }
    const propStr = String(property);
    if (propStr.startsWith('VITE_')) {
      return getEnvClient()[propStr as keyof EnvClient];
    }
    return getEnvServer()[propStr as keyof EnvServer];
  },
});
```

_⚠️ Potential issue_ | _🟠 Major_ | _⚡ Quick win_

**Cursor calculation skips one record between pages.**

At Line 155 and Line 309, `nextCursor` is derived from the overflow row that you then `pop()`. Because the next query uses strict boundary filters, that row is dropped permanently.




<details>
<summary>💡 Proposed fix</summary>

```diff
       let nextCursor: UserId | undefined;
       if (rows.length > input.limit) {
-        const nextItem = rows.pop();
-        nextCursor = nextItem ? toUserId(nextItem.id) : undefined;
+        rows.pop();
+        const lastVisible = rows[rows.length - 1];
+        nextCursor = lastVisible ? toUserId(lastVisible.id) : undefined;
       }
```

```diff
       let nextCursor: SessionId | undefined;
       if (rows.length > input.limit) {
-        const nextItem = rows.pop();
-        nextCursor = nextItem ? toSessionId(nextItem.id) : undefined;
+        rows.pop();
+        const lastVisible = rows[rows.length - 1];
+        nextCursor = lastVisible ? toSessionId(lastVisible.id) : undefined;
       }
```
</details>


Also applies to: 309-313

<details>
<summary>🤖 Prompt for AI Agents</summary>

```
Verify each finding against current code. Fix only still-valid issues, skip the
rest with a brief reason, keep changes minimal, and validate.

In `@src/modules/user/infrastructure/drizzle/user-repository-drizzle.ts` around
lines 155 - 159, The current pagination code computes nextCursor from the
overflow row by popping it (nextCursor = toUserId(rows.pop().id)), which mutates
rows and causes the overflow record to be dropped and skipped on the next page;
instead, when you fetch limit+1 rows, set nextCursor = toUserId(rows[rows.length
- 1].id) (or toUserId(rows[input.limit].id)) from the extra row without removing
it, then slice the returned results to rows.slice(0, input.limit) for the
response; update the logic around nextCursor, rows and toUserId in
user-repository-drizzle.ts so the overflow row is preserved for cursor
calculation and only the returned page is truncated.
```

</details>

